[VS2-329] Criteria and rules for Data Collection assets

Background:
When controlling who can access which data assets, R&D Data Provisioning Operations (DPO) need clear, consistent rules based on well-defined asset properties (metadata) like classification level, business unit, or data type. Using stable metadata ensures that anyone running the same access query gets the same list of assets every time, which is essential for policy setting and automated access controls that work without human involvement. During the Data Collection assets definition setup, it is crucial to have complete, unambiguous lists that clearly identify which assets are included or excluded. Furthermore, when asset properties change such as when a file is updated from "Consented" to "Consent withdrawn", these changes must automatically update access permissions within minutes to ensure security controls stay current and Scientists do not retain access they should not have.

User Story:
As a DPO officer, I want access criteria to map to stable metadata fields so that asset lists are unambiguous and reproducible.

Acceptance criteria:
GIVEN an Open Data Collection access criteria WHEN defining them using metadata fields THEN the criteria to point to unambiguous list of assets AND the asset list is reproduceable.
GIVEN an Open Data Collection access criteria WHEN they reference metadata fields THEN they are stable and explicit
GIVEN Open Data Collection assets WHEN input criteria are provided THEN list of study d-codes OR Study IDs are listed.
GIVEN an Open Data Collection asset WHEN access criteria for it is defined THEN the system automatically flags assets that are "Out of Scope" or "Restricted" based on metadata.